result.execSummary:
The defendant Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones was found guilty of Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:

The Court ordered defendant to serve 15 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to case # 15CM931 and to any other sentence, with credit for 0 (zero) days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges, pursuant to 303.08 Wis. Stats. for inmate work at House of Corrections, treatment and UWM Program ONLY:

Court ordered defendant to pay all mandatory court costs and fees by October 16, 2017, or to be docketed as a civil judgment. Court ordered non-mandatory costs WAIVED.

Filed;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.

Defendant Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones in court with attorney Francisco Araiza.  Defendant Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones in custody.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.

AS TO COUNT 1:

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the criminal complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  

AS TO COUNT 2:

On motion of the State, Court ordered count dismissed.

Attorney Torrie R. Williams in court, defendant Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones not in court, in custody.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter calendared for Plea and sentencing.  Parties informed that Branch 37 is in jury trial and unable to hear this matter on today; adjourned date selected.  Agreed Upon Request for a New Court Date is signed and filed.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for October 15, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Victoria's Secret (anywhere) and Bayshore Town Mall.
Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  Court ordered absolute sobriety.

Defendant Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones in court with attorney Torrie R. Williams.  Defendant Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones in custody.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty. Case remains set for plea and sentencing on 08/26/2015 8:30.

Attorney Torrie R. Williams in court, defendant Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones not in court, in custody.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for adjourned initial appearance but the defendant is not produced. Defense has received discovery. Case adjourned to Branch 37.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for August 4, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 26, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Andrea Mary Cloud-Jones not in court.   No Assistant District Attorney Available appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Both files are being sent to Branch 37, Judge Dee. She has a lower pending case on Monday 8-3-2015, at 8:30 am. (15CM93).  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.
